<p>We apply a mechanistic model that describes TKI response as a dynamic process resulting from the interplay between tumor growth, activation/deactivation of LSCs, and cytotoxic TKI action on proliferating, but not on quiescent LSCs (
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="f1-1031825">Figure 1A</xref>). The model is a simplification of our previous computational CML model
 <sup>
  <xref rid="b5-1031825" ref-type="bibr">5</xref>,
  <xref rid="b17-1031825" ref-type="bibr">17</xref>
 </sup> and formally related to a model proposed by Komarova and Wodarz.
 <sup>
  <xref rid="b22-1031825" ref-type="bibr">22</xref>
 </sup> It considers three leukemic cell types: quiescent LSCs (
 <italic>X</italic>), proliferating LSCs (
 <italic>Y</italic>), and fully differentiated LCs (
 <italic>W</italic>). Mathematically, the model is described by the following set of differential equations: 
 <disp-formula id="fd2-1031825">
  <math id="mm2">
   <mrow>
    <mfrac>
     <mrow>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mi>X</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mi>t</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mo>−</mo>
    <msub>
     <mi>p</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mi>X</mi>
      <mi>Y</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mi>X</mi>
    <mo>+</mo>
    <msub>
     <mi>P</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mi>Y</mi>
      <mi>X</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mi>Y</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
  <label>(E2)</label>
 </disp-formula>
 <disp-formula id="fd3-1031825">
  <math id="mm3">
   <mrow>
    <mfrac>
     <mrow>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mi>Y</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mi>t</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <msub>
     <mi>p</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mi>X</mi>
      <mi>Y</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mi>X</mi>
    <mo>−</mo>
    <msub>
     <mi>p</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mi>Y</mi>
      <mi>X</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mi>Y</mi>
    <mo>+</mo>
    <msub>
     <mi>p</mi>
     <mi>Y</mi>
    </msub>
    <mi>Y</mi>
    <mo>−</mo>
    <msub>
     <mi>e</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>K</mi>
      <mi>I</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mi>Y</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
  <label>(E3)</label>
 </disp-formula>
